Isolation Source: febrile patient on Flinders Island, Australia
Isolation Comments: isolated from a febrile patient on Flinders Island, Australia in 1991, and has been proposed for Flinders Island spotted fever group (FISF) agent which is pathogenic for humans and is transmitted to human by tick bites
Comments: R. honei strain RB has been isolated from a febrile patient on Flinders Island, Australia in 1991, and has been proposed for Flinders Island spotted fever group (FISF) agent which is pathogenic for humans and is transmitted to human by tick bites.

Sequencing Centers: Laboratory of Bacterial Genomics, Pathogen Genomics Center, National Institute of Infectious Diseases
Comments: A 60-year-old Japanese woman developed fever, headache, skin rash, and altered vision after returning from India. We detected elevated antibody titers for spotted fever group rickettsia. A polymerase chain reaction test yielded positive results for rickettsial ompA. A unique rickettsial agent was isolated from the blood. Full-genome analysis ensued.

Isolation Comments: isolated from a human in South Africa
Comments: Rickettsia conorii strain Malish 7. This strain was isolated from a human in South Africa.

Isolation Comments: isolated from a typhus patient in Madrid
Comments: Rickettsia prowazekii strain Madrid E. This strain is an egg-passaged attentuated avirulent strain that has been used as a live vaccine and was originally isolated from a typhus patient in Madrid.

Sequencing Centers: Institute for Systems Biology|University of Iowa
Isolation Source: from a patient with Rocky Mountain spotted fever
Isolation Comments: isolated from from a patient with Rocky Mountain spotted fever and will be used for comparative analysis
Comments: Rickettsia rickettsii str. 'Sheila Smith'. This strain was isolated from from a patient with Rocky Mountain spotted fever and will be used for comparative analysis.
